  "text": "SDN is a relatively recent networking paradigm that facilitates new innovative and flexible networking environments. SDNs provide an opportunity for network administrators and service providers to add new service-specific functionality for monitoring and management in order to improve the QoS/QoE for their subscribers [CITATION_1] . Currently, the most common protocol for communication between the controller and the data plane is OpenFlow, and many network vendors already implement it in their components.",
